I don't agree with your assertion, but I think it's a fair point. I like the blinking and snapping combo because I like the idea of this SCP being centered around a teenager trying to help his brother who had no idea what he was getting into. It does make the logs more complex, maybe a tad more arduous - but I was trying to hammer home the idea that by having a complex combo and literally blinking in and out of existence at the whims of the people interviewing him, this kid was going to have a tougher road to hoe, and all for art that needed to be explained way too much. My fear was that if I made it simpler, or made it so he could conceivably stay there until you snapped again, it would undermine that idea. You don't have to snap constantly, but everyone has to blink. It's a situation that sucks, especially for a kid who's still afraid of the dark.







